Package view

package view
  • Class
    Description
    Action
    The Action interface provides a single method, onAction, which is intended to encapsulate any action or behavior that needs to be executed.
    CardView
    CardView is an ImageView representing a card in a game, capable of displaying different images based on the card's state and animating flips between these states.
    GameGUI
     
    GameView
    GameView is a BorderPane that displays a game board and handles game interactions, including theme changes and game restarts.
    LoginScreen
    A custom login screen layout for managing user authentication and account creation.
    Observer
    The Observer interface defines a method for receiving updates from an observed object.
    SettingsPane
    SettingsPane is a BorderPane that allows users to select and apply themes from a list.
    StartScreen
    A customized start screen layout containing a background image and a play button.
    StatsScreen
    A customized grid layout for displaying statistical information related to a player's game performance.
